# {{OWNER}}'s AIOS Workspace — agent guide

Portable instructions for **all** agent runtimes (Claude Code, OpenCode, Codex, Cursor).
The owner-facing overview lives in [`.claude/CLAUDE.md`](.claude/CLAUDE.md) — read it for
spine layout, access tiers, skills, and Team Brain sync.

## Git & workflow (mandatory)

**This repo is {{OWNER}}'s personal workstation, not the AIOS product repo.** Optimize for
fast context work — not branch hygiene or merge archaeology.

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| Work on `master`; commit when {{OWNER}} asks | Create branches or worktrees here by default |
| Write notes, drafts, and dogfood findings in the spine | Stage toolkit code here for upstream PRs |
| Implement toolkit fixes in **`aios-workspace`** | Switch branches or merge without explicit instruction |

**Dogfood notes here; toolkit PRs in `aios-workspace` only.**

- Observations, friction logs, onboarding feedback → `2-work/`, `3-log/`, etc. (this repo, `master`).
- Scaffold, onboarding, GUI, validators, shared agent contracts → **`aios-workspace`** (branch there if needed; PR upstream; refresh this instance after merge).

Full rule: [`.claude/rules/git-workflow.md`](.claude/rules/git-workflow.md).

