## Team Brain

If `aios.yaml` has a `brain_url`, tier-tagged content syncs via `aios status|push|pull|query`.
`private` and untagged content never leaves this machine.

## Agent layer

The `.claude/` directory is the **canonical, runtime-agnostic agent layer**. Despite the
name, its skills, rules, rubrics, and commands are designed for all agent runtimes
(Claude Code, OpenCode, Codex), not just Claude Code. Skills degrade honestly on
non-Claude runtimes per BYOA's export contract.

## OpenCode-native tools

When using OpenCode in this workspace:

- **Project config:** `opencode.json` — default agent, governance instructions, permissions
- **Project agents:** `.opencode/agents/` — `aios-orchestrator` (primary), plus workflow subagents
- **Commands:** `.opencode/command/` — exported from `.claude/commands/`
- **Instincts plugin:** `.opencode/plugins/aios-instincts.ts` — access gate and session checks

Install plugin deps once: `cd .opencode && npm install`

